comments:
To use the MonteCarloAnalysis Block Analysis, please proceed with the following steps:

  1. Inherited from “MonteCarloAnalysis”: create an inherited block from the “MonteCarloAnalysis” block. We'll call it "MCAnalysis" block. Inherited value properties (4) will be assigned to the "MCAnalysis" block during the execution (real-time updated).
  2. Create BoundReference property: a value property must be applied with BoundReference Normal stereotypes as the main simulation context of the analysis in the "MCAnalysis" block.
  3. Create IBD: Internal Block Diagram must be created in the "MCAnalysis" block to bind the BoundReference with a value of the part property, and statistical value with a value property. Also "OutOfSpec" must be connected to a constraint properly.
  4. Create a SimulationConfig: executionTarget to the "MCAnalysis" block, set numberOfRun (e.g. 5000), and other tags, e.g. resultLocation.
  5. Set Histogram and CSV Export: create a histogram and CSV Export, and drag into the SimulationConfig.
  • OutOfSpec: % of samples violating any of the attached constraints/requirements.
  • N: statistical value, the number of observations/ data points from a Monte-Carlo simulation.
  • Mean: statistical value, an average of observations/ data points from a Monte-Carlo simulation.
  • Deviation: statistical value, a standard deviation of observations/ data points from a Monte-Carlo simulation.

comments:
To use the TradeStudy Block Analysis, please proceed with the following steps:

  1. Inherited from “TradeStudy”: create an inherited block from the “TradeStudy” block. We'll call it "TradeAnalysis" block. Inherited value properties (4) will be assigned to the “TradeAnalysis” block during the execution (real-time updated).
  2. Create part property: a part property must be created as the main simulation context of the trade study in the "TradeAnalysis" block.
    Create objectiveFunction: a constraint property which applied objectiveFunction should be created as a part of the "TradeAnalysis" block.
  3. Create alternatives: reference properties which applied alternatives must be specified in the "TradeAnalysis" block.
  4. Create IBD: Internal Block Diagram must be created in the "TradeAnalysis" block to bind "score" and objectiveFunction. Also "kind" and "source" tags must be specified properly.
  5. Create a SimulationConfig: set executionTarget to the "TradeAnalysis" block, and other tags, e.g. resultLocation, silent.
  • OutOfSpec: % of samples violating any of the attached constraints/requirements.
  • N: the number of configurations which have been evaluated.
  • score: the winner value as of specified objectiveFunction.
  • winner: the winner configuration from specified alternatives.
documentation:
To use the TradeStudy Block Analysis, please proceed with the following steps:

  1. Inherited from “TradeStudy”: create an inherited block from the “TradeStudy” block. We'll call it "TradeAnalysis" block. Inherited value properties (4) will be assigned to the “TradeAnalysis” block during the execution (real-time updated).
  2. Create part property: a part property must be created as the main simulation context of the trade study in the "TradeAnalysis" block.
    Create objectiveFunction: a constraint property which applied objectiveFunction should be created as a part of the "TradeAnalysis" block.
  3. Create alternatives: reference properties which applied alternatives must be specified in the "TradeAnalysis" block.
  4. Create IBD: Internal Block Diagram must be created in the "TradeAnalysis" block to bind "score" and objectiveFunction. Also "kind" and "source" tags must be specified properly.
  5. Create a SimulationConfig: set executionTarget to the "TradeAnalysis" block, and other tags, e.g. resultLocation, silent.
  • OutOfSpec: % of samples violating any of the attached constraints/requirements.
  • N: the number of configurations which have been evaluated.
  • score: the winner value as of specified objectiveFunction.
  • winner: the winner configuration from specified alternatives.
